[SN]TITLE[SN]
Kevin De Bruyne: Man City signing stars in win for Belgium

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Manchester City club record Â£55m buy Kevin De Bruyne scored as Belgium came from behind to beat Bosnia-Herzegovina at home in their Euro 2016 qualifier.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
City striker Edin Dzeko, who is on loan at Roma, headed the visitors ahead.
But Belgium scored twice in 20 minutes before half-time, Manchester United midfielder Marouane Fellaini nodding home from De Bruyne's corner before the latter's turn and shot made it 2-1.
Chelsea's Eden Hazard won and converted a penalty to seal the points.
Belgium, who remain second in the group, are three points behind leaders Wales with three games remaining.
They are two points ahead of third-placed Israel - with the top two in the group qualifying for next summer's tournament in France.
Belgium's last three games are away to Cyprus on 6 September and away to Andorra on 10 October before hosting Israel three days later.
Elsewhere in Group B, Israel defeated bottom side Andorra 4-0 at home.
